      "content": "That's exactly what I suspected. The fact that the 1933 Non-Recognition Pact exists but is basically buried in footnotes proves there was a coordinated effort to erase us. I actually have the original decree from my grandfather, the previous head of the house, which outlines the specific succession rights tied to the Altyni bloodline. \n\nIf I were to present these documents to an international legal body or even a private tribunal, how would the principle of 'uti possidetis juris' apply to a state that was forcibly removed from the map? I need to know how to bridge the gap between my family's documented lineage and current international recognition.",
